    "A central aim of their review was to analyse how user studies are currently implemented and provide suggestions for future studies.",
    "To manage this thematic breadth, the authors only performed a coarsegrained automatic literature search of selected conferences.",
    "In consequence, the number of included publications that dealt with the performance effects of saliency maps for image classification is rather low.",
    "While the authors report mixed findings regarding the effects of XAI on performance, the small number and large variability of included studies does not allow them to explain these inconsistencies.",
    "A similarly broad review has been presented by Haque et al. (2023)."
